snippet.textDisplay:
For those new to Tabletop RPGs, especially those who have played the related video games, I highly recommend the Dragon Age system as being one of the best to get started. It uses three 6 sided dice, and a system of "stunts" instead of criticals. While easy to learn at the start it also gains a lot more complexity and depth as you play more of it and level up with new skills etc. There are a good number of pre written quests for various levels that I cannot recommend highly enough.

We play Dragln Age most Fridays, 5th Edition D&D every Saturday, every other Sunday, and sometimes in between, and we sometimes play Star Wars Saga Edition on Wednesdays. Star Wars Saga is the most complex system and is a pain, but does allow room to create really in depth characters with unique skill sets and uses the d20 system at the centre (it's like an upgrade to Core Edition, which itself was actually used for the video game Knights of the Old Republic as the gameplay framework).

I love tabletop RPGs a lot. I'm disabled and can't go out much, so having friends come here and sit around the table with me, or even play online using Roll20 and Discord, it is fantastic to socialise and also keep my mind off the chronic pain.
